ight need to delete or rename it, or possibly write a new file instead. The top-level public class must match the path. Since there’s just the test file, I could change the class name to Maven_xmlTest, but it feels a bit off. I should check checkstyle for class name rules, especially since the existing generated name seems to fit. I'll also consider if using an underscore in a public class name could be an issue.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_q40xeG7Q35XMQa74xiEe8taV|fc_0d16fa1825d8fb610169fd83d7da908194a6aab4b81fd2a73f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -path '*/src/test/java/*' -name '*_Test.java' -o -name '*xml*Test.java' | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2317, "output": 1193, "cacheRead": 41984, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45494, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778222018793, "responseId": "resp_0d16fa1825d8fb610169fd83c43118819488b9b5d1015ee881"}}
